article.headline: Yale 73, Sacred Heart 59
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Alex Gamboa scored 17 points and Scott Gaffield added 13 to lead Yale to a 73-59 win over Sacred Heart on Thursday. The Bulldogs (4-2) used a 30-7 run midway through the second half to put away the Pioneers (2-3) in a game that had six lead changes and five ties. Yale scored 17 points on free throws during the run and finished 27 of 40 from the line. The Bulldogs outrebounded Sacred Heart, 47-35, getting 11 offensive rebounds in the second half. Paul Vitelli dominated inside for Yale, grabbing 11 boards. Dominick Martin, who missed his first five shots, finished with 10 points for the Bulldogs. Senior guard Maurice Bailey led the Pioneers with 16 points and senior guard Omar Wellington added 13 for Sacred Heart. Mading Mading led Sacred Heart with nine rebounds.
